The paper deals with proof-search tactics in logic and type theory, which are topics that are typically studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses sequent calculi and their organization for effective proof-search, which falls under the category of computational logic (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of interactive proof construction, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
